00:08:20.790 --> 00:08:25.900
Then let's get to the main
subject we want to discuss now.

00:08:25.900 --> 00:08:28.900
And these are actually
Feynman diagrams.

00:08:28.900 --> 00:08:35.799
I wanted to give you
an exact definition

00:08:35.799 --> 00:08:38.299
and a deep
understanding, what does

00:08:38.299 --> 00:08:42.390
it mean when we talk about
processes of absorption

00:08:42.390 --> 00:08:47.500
and emission, but also about
absorption, emission processes

00:08:47.500 --> 00:08:49.820
which violate energy.

00:08:49.820 --> 00:08:53.440
And some people refer to
them as virtual photons.

00:08:53.440 --> 00:08:59.480
The reason is that virtual
photons cannot really exist

00:08:59.480 --> 00:09:01.490
for a long time.

00:09:01.490 --> 00:09:04.040
When you emit a virtual
photon, another photon

00:09:04.040 --> 00:09:06.950
has to be absorbed immediately
to reconcile energy

00:09:06.950 --> 00:09:09.560
conservation, as we
want to see in a moment.

00:09:09.560 --> 00:09:13.980
So the goal of this
presentation is

00:09:13.980 --> 00:09:18.320
I want you that you realize
that each of those doodles

00:09:18.320 --> 00:09:20.610
has an exact
mathematical meaning.

00:09:23.900 --> 00:09:28.465
Each of those diagrams
represents one term,

00:09:28.465 --> 00:09:32.660
or a class of terms,
in an exact solution

00:09:32.660 --> 00:09:36.780
for the time evolution
of the system.

00:09:36.780 --> 00:09:49.870
So in other words,
if you would ask me,

00:09:49.870 --> 00:09:52.360
we have a ground
and excited state.

00:09:52.360 --> 00:09:56.210
Is it possible that the
ground state emits a photon,

00:09:56.210 --> 00:09:58.860
goes to a virtual state,
emits another photon

00:09:58.860 --> 00:10:04.400
of another frequency, and then
somehow absorbs the photon,

00:10:04.400 --> 00:10:10.300
goes to here, and eventually
takes another photon,

00:10:10.300 --> 00:10:12.700
and is back to the ground state.

00:10:12.700 --> 00:10:14.200
Is that a possibility?

00:10:14.200 --> 00:10:15.900
Can that happen?

00:10:15.900 --> 00:10:18.330
And I think what
the message here

00:10:18.330 --> 00:10:21.130
is yes, everything happens.

00:10:21.130 --> 00:10:24.790
The system is trying out
all of its possibility.

00:10:24.790 --> 00:10:27.820
And the two time
evolution is the sum

00:10:27.820 --> 00:10:31.500
of all those possibilities,
of all the amplitudes related

00:10:31.500 --> 00:10:33.270
to those diagrams.

00:10:33.270 --> 00:10:36.750
But what I want to show you
is how sort of the weirder

00:10:36.750 --> 00:10:40.480
the diagrams get, the more you
go in energy below the ground

00:10:40.480 --> 00:10:44.150
state, the more you go away
from real atomic states,

00:10:44.150 --> 00:10:46.390
the bigger is your
energy denominator.

00:10:46.390 --> 00:10:48.930
And that means
those diagrams have

00:10:48.930 --> 00:10:50.840
a smaller and smaller weight.

00:10:50.840 --> 00:10:57.120
And in all practical
calculations, we neglect those.

00:10:57.120 --> 00:11:01.030
But I want you sort of to be
able to see that and realize,

00:11:01.030 --> 00:11:02.920
I exactly know what it means.

00:11:02.920 --> 00:11:05.800
It means this and this
term in a summation

00:11:05.800 --> 00:11:07.802
over all the amplitudes
which the quantum

00:11:07.802 --> 00:11:08.635
system is exploring.

00:11:11.065 --> 00:11:13.690
And I think with that, we really
learn something about physics.

00:11:13.690 --> 00:11:16.830
We learn about what is
actually inside the Schrodinger

00:11:16.830 --> 00:11:19.120
equation.

00:11:19.120 --> 00:11:22.990
A lot of people actually,
before they take this class,

00:11:22.990 --> 00:11:24.460
think that this
is just nonsense,

00:11:24.460 --> 00:11:26.060
that this has no
physical reality.

00:11:26.060 --> 00:11:28.000
But I hope after
this class, you see

00:11:28.000 --> 00:11:31.770
that pretty much everything
you draw has physical reality.

00:11:31.770 --> 00:11:34.580
It's just-- it may
not contribute a lot.

00:11:41.630 --> 00:11:46.600
So what we have done--
and let me just start here

00:11:46.600 --> 00:11:49.660
and invite your questions.

00:11:49.660 --> 00:11:53.340
We have figured out how
an initial state evolves

00:11:53.340 --> 00:11:57.810
with a time evolution operator
to another basis state,

00:11:57.810 --> 00:11:59.640
toward the final state.

00:11:59.640 --> 00:12:06.090
And formally, this is the formal
solution and exact solution

00:12:06.090 --> 00:12:08.220
of the Schrodinger equation.

00:12:08.220 --> 00:12:14.491
We have to sum over all orders,
orders in the interaction.

00:12:14.491 --> 00:12:16.130
Well, I will
immediately tell you

00:12:16.130 --> 00:12:18.000
what is the first
and second order.

00:12:18.000 --> 00:12:19.310
We are not going much higher.

00:12:19.310 --> 00:12:22.170
But if you want, here, you can.

00:12:22.170 --> 00:12:25.980
And then what you have to
do is in the time evolution,

00:12:25.980 --> 00:12:28.540
you have to sum over
intermediate times.

00:12:28.540 --> 00:12:31.910
You have to allow the system to
propagate, to change its state,

00:12:31.910 --> 00:12:34.260
propagate again,
change its state again.

00:12:34.260 --> 00:12:40.080
And the times where the
change of state happens,

00:12:40.080 --> 00:12:43.570
that can happen at any
time between your initial

00:12:43.570 --> 00:12:44.900
and your final time.

00:12:44.900 --> 00:12:49.470
And we integrate over
all possible times.

00:12:49.470 --> 00:12:51.060
And I showed you--
and I think this

00:12:51.060 --> 00:12:54.520
was the very last thing
we did on Wednesday.

00:12:54.520 --> 00:12:58.390
I showed you how
this diagram can

00:12:58.390 --> 00:13:02.754
be translated into
mathematical equation.

00:13:02.754 --> 00:13:04.670
And I think I picked the
second order diagram.

00:13:04.670 --> 00:13:08.000
But I think from the way how I
presented should be clear now

00:13:08.000 --> 00:13:13.580
how any such diagram can be
translated into an equation.

00:13:13.580 --> 00:13:16.010
And eventually, you have
to perform an integral

00:13:16.010 --> 00:13:17.647
over all intermediate times.

00:13:17.647 --> 00:13:19.855
And this is part of the time
evolution of the system.

